items.name: Evan Rachel Wood (JG)
items.description:
Evan Rachel Wood is an American actress, winner of Golden Globe and Emmy awards, mostly known for her role as Dolores Abernathy in the HBO series Westworld.

135-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (rew00d:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.description:
Model created after Getbackers' Kuroudo Akabane, the mysterious tall man with the large black hat. The model comes in two versions. One is severely underbaked and one's severely overbaked. The results may vary, of course, but in my opinion, the underbaked version far surpasses the overbaked one.


The overbaked one, however, seems to be more competent at making him use his iconic weapons like his Bloody Sword but the face becomes a little distorted and his eyes have an eerie glow to them. There is not particular trigger word for the overbaked version but describing him is strongly recommended. See the example images to understand what I mean.


The model works the best when paired with other Loras. Sebastian's from Kuroshitsuji seems to be a perfect fit but also one that recently came out called Manhwa male face.

items.name: MK11 - Frost [LoRA]
items.description:
"Chilled to the core!"

This LoRA is based on the character Frost from Mortal Kombat 11.

- There is already a LoRA of her by True_Might, what are you bringing to the table?

True_Might did a good job, but I am not a fan of how Frost`s outfit looks in MKDA, my LoRA is much more SFW oriented and produces results that are faithful to a more grounded MK11 aesthetic. I have fine tuned the dataset to include some misc. fanart of Frost that I like, but trying to stick to her ingame appearance with a few headcanon exceptions.

Recommended tags:

spiked hair, ((mask)) or ((cybernetic mask)), gaze, implants, ((cybernetic body)) (if you want that look)

Strenghts:

  • Cyborg body? Human body? A mix of both? Go nuts!

  • Can handle a variety of hairstyles.

  • Performs best on 2.5D checkpoints. Works decently in photorealism (with some weight adjustments).

  • Compatible with almost any other style LoRA, negative embedding, etc.

Weak points:

  • Sometimes the cybernetic mask may look more like a medical mask. This is only visible around the ears. Putting "medical mask" in negative prompt solves it most of the time.

  • Since a big chunk of the dataset is from the game, perfomance on purely 2D/Anime checkpoints is so-so in terms of artstyle consistency. If LoRA pulls your expected 2D output to 2.5D, try either dropping the weight or adding a style LoRA on top.

items.name: Memo-Ray
items.description:
Memo-Ray is a anime model finetuned on ACertainty.Carefully selected many characters and illustration images for training purposes.Improved certain issues present in traditional anime models.

Compared to the Merge model, the Merge model tends to be overfitted. It does not always adhere to your prompts and may add irrelevant details. In contrast, the finetune model does not have these issues.

Feature:

  • Trained on 768 resolution.Useing higher base resolution to generate images.

  • Better eyes details.

  • Better silk stockings texture.

  • Offset noise.

  • Better background And scenery

  • Better time concept. addresses the limitations in accurately generating night, twilight.

  • Not merge

Of course, there are many other aspects of this model that I haven't specified. However, given the limitations imposed by Civitai's guidelines, I cannot provide further details here. Including NSFW content. I will not provide further details on this matter.You are encouraged to explore and discover them on your own.

NOTE:

I strongly recommend using hire.fix to generate images.

Because of offset noise include the model,so it is not compatible with LoRA that also include offset noise.An evident manifestation would be color distortion and blurred images. If you insist on using both, the suggested solution is to download the offset noise lora and set the weight to a negative value, such as -1 or -2.

And refrain from using this Lora when using the model under normal circumstances.

If you wish to merge this model and release, please mark out the model.

Introduce_CN

Memo-Ray是在ACertainty上微调的动漫模型。精心挑选了许多人物、插画图片进行训练。改进了一些传统动漫模型的问题。

相对于Merge模型，Merge模型往往会过拟合。它并不总是遵循您的提示，并可能添加不相关的细节。相比之下，微调模型没有这些问题。

Feature:

  • 训练时采用768分辨率。请采用更高基础分辨率进行图像生成。

  • 改进了眼睛细节。

  • 改进丝袜材质。

  • Offset noise.

  • 更好的背景和风景效果。

  • 更好的时间概念。 解决了画黄昏、夜晚困难的问题。

  • Not merge

当然，还有模型的许多其他方面我没有具体说明。然而，考虑到Civitai的限制，我无法在此提供进一步的细节。包括NSFW内容，我不会在这里进行说明。建议您自行探索和发现。

items.name: Billions of Constructions - Standalone Extension, buildings, rooms, etc.
items.description:
With YAML-files you just get 1 nice wildcard-file Instead of 100 files. They are easy readable (best with Notepadd++) and they are easy to maintain.

The wildcards follow the same scheme as the Billions of Construction wildcards. You can use them together. However, this set has no dependencies within BoChars.

Don't forget to leave a ❤️ to get a notification for future updates. ⭐ reviews are appreciated, too. Let me see what you created with this tool. ;)

note: Yaml files will throw isseus when using: "a1111-sd-webui-tagcomplete"extension. That's related to the extension, not the wildcards.

Usage

Unleash the full power:

Activate: Dynamic Prompts->Advanced Options->Unlink seed from prompt

Usage is pretty much the same as for "regular" wildcards.

You need the SD Dynamic Prompt Extension. Put the files directly into the wildcard folder:

~\stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards

They show up as a menu on the left in the Wildcards tab.

The YAML is structured and indented (that's how they work). Just with a little difference. You have to add the category layers in the wildcard.

Examples:

__BoConstructions/random__
__BoConstructions/random-room__
__BoConstructions/random-building__

A cool thing you can do, too, is using a wildcard "*" in the wildcards. So you could use the normal chararcter wildcards in the same prompt and get chars from both sets:

__properties/patterns/*__    # you'll get all patterns from my other sets
__properties/materials*/*__  # you'll get all materials from my other sets

I made easy to use wildcards for building and room creations.

There might be some wildcards that are not used for it. Have a look what's in there, too. You'll find a full list below. You can use each subcategory separately.

You are welcome

Leave a star review, if you like it. so other can find those awesome cards more easily.

I plan to add more themes as extensions in the future. SDXL is coming, and wildcards are limitless.

If you want to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. ;)

Have experimenting with it.

items.name: Helios 44 - swirly vintage bokeh
items.description:
Helios camera lenses were produced in the former Soviet Union from the 1950s to the 1990s. The most popular models were the 58mm f/2 Helios 44 series lenses, based on the revolutionary Carl Zeiss Biotar (aided by plans and machinery taken from the Zeiss plant in occupied East Germany).

The earliest Helios 44 lenses had 13 aperture blades. When the aperture was fully open, these blades created a dreamy, swirled bokeh effect in out-of-focus areas. Later models had eight or six blades, but the design of the lenses still allowed for a striking bokeh effect.

In recent years, Helios 44 lenses have experienced a resurge in popularity as an affordable entry point to retro photography. The lomography movement and associated aesthetic celebrates the analogue imperfections of vintage Russian cameras.

This LoRA was trained on photographs taken by a range of Helios 44 lenses, and reproduces the trademark swirly bokeh and centre sharpness of the Soviet glass.

Two versions of this model are available: one trained against the base SD1.5 model, and one trained against a specialised cartoon-style checkpoint. The former will work well with base SD1.5 and photorealistic checkpoints, the latter will work better for Western animation and anime style checkpoints.
